{
  "text": "Treating VSMCs with Ang II leads to altered HIF-1\u2423 proline hydroxylation, decreased pVHL binding, reduced HIF-1\u2423 ubiquitination, and proteasomal degradation leading to increased HIF-1\u2423 stabilization [CITATION_1] . ROS generation plays a pivotal role in these Ang II-mediated effects on the HIF-1 system. Our current work now identifies mitochondrial-derived ROS as essential intermediates leading to the stabilization of HIF-1\u2423, the activation of HIF-1, increased in HIF-1 target gene expression, and associated cellular effects, such as VSMC migration.",
